Description: Just a great guitar! This is a 2005 model and she’s really clean. The only blemish I can find is a hairline paint indent by the lower F hole, it wouldn’t photograph. Extremely clean for a 2005 and these are made miles better than the Eddie Cochran signatures these days. I need a SG or I wouldn’t let go of it. A cool guitar with rockabilly style, this Gretsch G6120W 1957 features an all maple body with an orange finish, oversize f-holes, and a G brand on the top. The bound rosewood fretboard has block inlays with Western engravings. It’s equipped with a DynaSonic single coil pickup in the bridge position and a Fralin dogear single coil pickup at the neck. I replaced the original bar bridge with a tonepros roller bridge assembly and what a huge upgrade. She stays in tune and perfectly intonated. The original bridge is included. If you’re looking for one of these...this would be the one. Orange finish All maple body Oversize (bound) f-hole and G brand on top Maple neck Bound rosewood fretboard Block inlays with Western engravings DynaSonic single coil pickup at bridge Fralin dogear single coil at neck Bigsby tailpiece and bridge Bound headstock Open gear tuners Dice knobs 1-11/16" nut 24-3/4" scale Original hardshell case
Title: Gretsch 6120 G6120w 1957 Eddie Cochran Hollowbody Guitar Rockabilly Fralin
